The paper proposes a new abstraction of normal form games called Feasibility/Desirability Games (FD Games) and discusses their applications in finding Nash equilibria, choice models in microeconomics, and evolutionary games. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Mechanism Design (cs.ME) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of decision makers as games, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the function that yields abstract Nash equilibria, which could fall under the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
